# lna config — synthetic example: a freelance studio deciding which inbound
# leads to work first. Copy to the repo root as lna.yaml and define YOUR
# mission precisely — judges estimate exactly the probability this line names.
# Quote every multi-word string (unquoted "word: word" is a YAML trap).

mission: "P(signed engagement within 60 days | we invest effort in this lead starting now)"

actor_context: >
  A two-person design studio. Can produce a tailored proposal or small spec
  sample in under a week; has strong client references in hospitality and
  retail; no existing relationships in enterprise software.

calibration:
  - "A referral or named internal champion is worth more than any document."
  - "Leads older than 30 days without contact have decayed sharply."
  - "A spec sample moves odds only when the lead named a concrete deliverable."

runs: 3
disagreement_spread: 20   # judges splitting >= this on either metric is flagged,
                          # not silently averaged
